The Voice of Conscience

Touch of grace
2013
Claudio Peri
(Photographer)
TOI take:
Published on: Jan 24, 2025
Pope Francis’s embrace of Vinicio Riva, a disfigured man, became a viral symbol of compassion and inclusivity. The image sparked discussions on acceptance, challenging societal stigmas surrounding physical appearance. It highlighted the power of compassion to inspire societal change, fostering empathy and promoting human dignity.
Echoes of terror
2013
Tyler Hicks
(Photographer)
TOI take:
Published on: Jan 13, 2025
The harrowing image from the 2013 Westgate Mall siege in Nairobi captures the human cost of terror—innocent lives caught in a violent crossfire. The tragedy, orchestrated by Al-Shabaab, exposed vulnerabilities in urban security and united global voices against terrorism, driving reforms in counterterrorism strategies and strengthening international cooperation to prevent such atrocities.
Surfing hippo
2000
Michael Nichols
(Photographer)
TOI take:
Published on: Jan 06, 2025
This photograph of a hippo in the Atlantic Ocean epitomizes the fragile intersection of wilderness and encroaching human presence. Capturing this rare scene during an epic trek, the image's impact transcended beauty—spurring Gabon’s President Omar Bongo to establish national parks, safeguarding 11% of the country for wildlife conservation and unspoiled nature.
